 2626      fn parse_match_expr(&mut self) -> @Expr {
 2627          let lo = self.last_span.lo;
 2628          let discriminant = self.parse_expr();
 2629          self.commit_expr_expecting(discriminant, token::LBRACE);
 2630          let mut arms: Vec<Arm> = Vec::new();
 2631          while self.token != token::RBRACE {
 2632              let pats = self.parse_pats();
 2633              let mut guard = None;
 2634              if self.eat_keyword(keywords::If) {
 2635                  guard = Some(self.parse_expr());
 2636              }
 2637              self.expect(&token::FAT_ARROW);
 2638              let expr = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_STMT_EXPR);
 2639  
 2640              let require_comma =
 2641                  !classify::expr_is_simple_block(expr)
 2642                  && self.token != token::RBRACE;
 2643  
 2644              if require_comma {
 2645                  self.commit_expr(expr, &[token::COMMA], &[token::RBRACE]);
 2646              } else {
 2647                  self.eat(&token::COMMA);
 2648              }
 2649  
 2650              arms.push(ast::Arm { pats: pats, guard: guard, body: expr });
 2651          }
 2652          let hi = self.span.hi;
 2653          self.bump();
 2654          return self.mk_expr(lo, hi, ExprMatch(discriminant, arms));
 2655      }

 2657      // parse an expression
 2658      pub fn parse_expr(&mut self) -> @Expr {
 2659          return self.parse_expr_res(UNRESTRICTED);
 2660      }

 2662      // parse an expression, subject to the given restriction
 2663      fn parse_expr_res(&mut self, r: restriction) -> @Expr {
 2664          let old = self.restriction;
 2665          self.restriction = r;
 2666          let e = self.parse_assign_expr();
 2667          self.restriction = old;
 2668          return e;
 2669      }

 2675              Some(self.parse_expr())
 2676          } else {
 2677              None
 2678          }
 2679      }

 2681      // parse patterns, separated by '|' s
 2682      fn parse_pats(&mut self) -> Vec<@Pat> {
 2683          let mut pats = Vec::new();
 2684          loop {
 2685              pats.push(self.parse_pat());
 2686              if self.token == token::BINOP(token::OR) { self.bump(); }
 2687              else { return pats; }
 2688          };
 2689      }
 2690  
 2691      fn parse_pat_vec_elements(
 2692          &mut self,
 2693      ) -> (Vec<@Pat> , Option<@Pat>, Vec<@Pat> ) {
 2694          let mut before = Vec::new();
 2695          let mut slice = None;
 2696          let mut after = Vec::new();
 2697          let mut first = true;
 2698          let mut before_slice = true;
 2699  
 2700          while self.token != token::RBRACKET {
 2701              if first { first = false; }
 2702              else { self.expect(&token::COMMA); }
 2703  
 2704              let mut is_slice = false;
 2705              if before_slice {
 2706                  if self.token == token::DOTDOT {
 2707                      self.bump();
 2708                      is_slice = true;
 2709                      before_slice = false;
 2710                  }
 2711              }
 2712  
 2713              if is_slice {
 2714                  if self.token == token::COMMA || self.token == token::RBRACKET {
 2715                      slice = Some(@ast::Pat {
 2716                          id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2717                          node: PatWildMulti,
 2718                          span: self.span,
 2719                      })
 2720                  } else {
 2721                      let subpat = self.parse_pat();
 2722                      match *subpat {
 2723                          ast::Pat { id, node: PatWild, span } => {
 2724                              self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteVecDotDotWildcard);
 2725                              slice = Some(@ast::Pat {
 2726                                  id: id,
 2727                                  node: PatWildMulti,
 2728                                  span: span
 2729                              })
 2730                          },
 2731                          ast::Pat { node: PatIdent(_, _, _), .. } => {
 2732                              slice = Some(subpat);
 2733                          }
 2734                          ast::Pat { span, .. } => self.span_fatal(
 2735                              span, "expected an identifier or nothing"
 2736                          )
 2737                      }
 2738                  }
 2739              } else {
 2740                  let subpat = self.parse_pat();
 2741                  if before_slice {
 2742                      before.push(subpat);
 2743                  } else {
 2744                      after.push(subpat);
 2745                  }
 2746              }
 2747          }
 2748  
 2749          (before, slice, after)
 2750      }

 2752      // parse the fields of a struct-like pattern
 2753      fn parse_pat_fields(&mut self) -> (Vec<ast::FieldPat> , bool) {
 2754          let mut fields = Vec::new();
 2755          let mut etc = false;
 2756          let mut first = true;
 2757          while self.token != token::RBRACE {
 2758              if first {
 2759                  first = false;
 2760              } else {
 2761                  self.expect(&token::COMMA);
 2762                  // accept trailing commas
 2763                  if self.token == token::RBRACE { break }
 2764              }
 2765  
 2766              etc = self.token == token::UNDERSCORE || self.token == token::DOTDOT;
 2767              if self.token == token::UNDERSCORE {
 2768                  self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteStructWildcard);
 2769              }
 2770              if etc {
 2771                  self.bump();
 2772                  if self.token != token::RBRACE {
 2773                      let token_str = self.this_token_to_str();
 2774                      self.fatal(format!("expected `\\}`, found `{}`",
 2775                                         token_str))
 2776                  }
 2777                  etc = true;
 2778                  break;
 2779              }
 2780  
 2781              let bind_type = if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Mut) {
 2782                  BindByValue(MutMutable)
 2783              } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Ref) {
 2784                  BindByRef(self.parse_mutability())
 2785              } else {
 2786                  BindByValue(MutImmutable)
 2787              };
 2788  
 2789              let fieldname = self.parse_ident();
 2790  
 2791              let subpat = if self.token == token::COLON {
 2792                  match bind_type {
 2793                      BindByRef(..) | BindByValue(MutMutable) => {
 2794                          let token_str = self.this_token_to_str();
 2795                          self.fatal(format!("unexpected `{}`", token_str))
 2796                      }
 2797                      _ => {}
 2798                  }
 2799  
 2800                  self.bump();
 2801                  self.parse_pat()
 2802              } else {
 2803                  let fieldpath = ast_util::ident_to_path(self.last_span,
 2804                                                          fieldname);
 2805                  @ast::Pat {
 2806                      id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2807                      node: PatIdent(bind_type, fieldpath, None),
 2808                      span: self.last_span
 2809                  }
 2810              };
 2811              fields.push(ast::FieldPat { ident: fieldname, pat: subpat });
 2812          }
 2813          return (fields, etc);
 2814      }
 2815  
 2816      // parse a pattern.
 2817      pub fn parse_pat(&mut self) -> @Pat {
 2818          maybe_whole!(self, NtPat);
 2819  
 2820          let lo = self.span.lo;
 2821          let mut hi;
 2822          let pat;
 2823          match self.token {
 2824              // parse _
 2825            token::UNDERSCORE => {
 2826              self.bump();
 2827              pat = PatWild;
 2828              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2829              return @ast::Pat {
 2830                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2831                  node: pat,
 2832                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2833              }
 2834            }
 2835            // parse @pat
 2836            token::AT => {
 2837              self.bump();
 2838              let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2839              self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteManagedPattern);
 2840              let hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2841              return @ast::Pat {
 2842                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2843                  node: PatUniq(sub),
 2844                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2845              }
 2846            }
 2847            token::TILDE => {
 2848              // parse ~pat
 2849              self.bump();
 2850              let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2851              pat = PatUniq(sub);
 2852              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2853              return @ast::Pat {
 2854                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2855                  node: pat,
 2856                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2857              }
 2858            }
 2859            token::BINOP(token::AND) => {
 2860                // parse &pat
 2861                let lo = self.span.lo;
 2862                self.bump();
 2863                let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2864                hi = sub.span.hi;
 2865                // HACK: parse &"..." as a literal of a borrowed str
 2866                pat = match sub.node {
 2867                    PatLit(e) => {
 2868                        match e.node {
 2869                          ExprLit(lit) if lit_is_str(lit) => {
 2870                            let vst = @Expr {
 2871                                id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2872                                node: ExprVstore(e, ExprVstoreSlice),
 2873                                span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2874                            };
 2875                            PatLit(vst)
 2876                          }
 2877                          _ => PatRegion(sub),
 2878                        }
 2879                    }
 2880                    _ => PatRegion(sub),
 2881              };
 2882              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2883              return @ast::Pat {
 2884                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2885                  node: pat,
 2886                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2887              }
 2888            }
 2889            token::LPAREN => {
 2890              // parse (pat,pat,pat,...) as tuple
 2891              self.bump();
 2892              if self.token == token::RPAREN {
 2893                  hi = self.span.hi;
 2894                  self.bump();
 2895                  let lit = @codemap::Spanned {
 2896                      node: LitNil,
 2897                      span: mk_sp(lo, hi)};
 2898                  let expr = self.mk_expr(lo, hi, ExprLit(lit));
 2899                  pat = PatLit(expr);
 2900              } else {
 2901                  let mut fields = vec!(self.parse_pat());
 2902                  if self.look_ahead(1, |t| *t != token::RPAREN) {
 2903                      while self.token == token::COMMA {
 2904                          self.bump();
 2905                          if self.token == token::RPAREN { break; }
 2906                          fields.push(self.parse_pat());
 2907                      }
 2908                  }
 2909                  if fields.len() == 1 { self.expect(&token::COMMA); }
 2910                  self.expect(&token::RPAREN);
 2911                  pat = PatTup(fields);
 2912              }
 2913              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2914              return @ast::Pat {
 2915                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2916                  node: pat,
 2917                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2918              }
 2919            }
 2920            token::LBRACKET => {
 2921              // parse [pat,pat,...] as vector pattern
 2922              self.bump();
 2923              let (before, slice, after) =
 2924                  self.parse_pat_vec_elements();
 2925  
 2926              self.expect(&token::RBRACKET);
 2927              pat = ast::PatVec(before, slice, after);
 2928              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2929              return @ast::Pat {
 2930                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2931                  node: pat,
 2932                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2933              }
 2934            }
 2935            _ => {}
 2936          }
 2937  
 2938          if !is_ident_or_path(&self.token)
 2939                  || self.is_keyword(keywords::True)
 2940                  || self.is_keyword(keywords::False) {
 2941              // Parse an expression pattern or exp .. exp.
 2942              //
 2943              // These expressions are limited to literals (possibly
 2944              // preceded by unary-minus) or identifiers.
 2945              let val = self.parse_literal_maybe_minus();
 2946              if self.eat(&token::DOTDOT) {
 2947                  let end = if is_ident_or_path(&self.token) {
 2948                      let path = self.parse_path(LifetimeAndTypesWithColons)
 2949                                     .path;
 2950                      let hi = self.span.hi;
 2951                      self.mk_expr(lo, hi, ExprPath(path))
 2952                  } else {
 2953                      self.parse_literal_maybe_minus()
 2954                  };
 2955                  pat = PatRange(val, end);
 2956              } else {
 2957                  pat = PatLit(val);
 2958              }
 2959          } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Mut) {
 2960              pat = self.parse_pat_ident(BindByValue(MutMutable));
 2961          } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Ref) {
 2962              // parse ref pat
 2963              let mutbl = self.parse_mutability();
 2964              pat = self.parse_pat_ident(BindByRef(mutbl));
 2965          } else {
 2966              let can_be_enum_or_struct = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 2967                  match *t {
 2968                      token::LPAREN | token::LBRACKET | token::LT |
 2969                      token::LBRACE | token::MOD_SEP => true,
 2970                      _ => false,
 2971                  }
 2972              });
 2973  
 2974              if self.look_ahead(1, |t| *t == token::DOTDOT) {
 2975                  let start = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_NO_BAR_OP);
 2976                  self.eat(&token::DOTDOT);
 2977                  let end = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_NO_BAR_OP);
 2978                  pat = PatRange(start, end);
 2979              } else if is_plain_ident(&self.token) && !can_be_enum_or_struct {
 2980                  let name = self.parse_path(NoTypesAllowed).path;
 2981                  let sub;
 2982                  if self.eat(&token::AT) {
 2983                      // parse foo @ pat
 2984                      sub = Some(self.parse_pat());
 2985                  } else {
 2986                      // or just foo
 2987                      sub = None;
 2988                  }
 2989                  pat = PatIdent(BindByValue(MutImmutable), name, sub);
 2990              } else {
 2991                  // parse an enum pat
 2992                  let enum_path = self.parse_path(LifetimeAndTypesWithColons)
 2993                                      .path;
 2994                  match self.token {
 2995                      token::LBRACE => {
 2996                          self.bump();
 2997                          let (fields, etc) =
 2998                              self.parse_pat_fields();
 2999                          self.bump();
 3000                          pat = PatStruct(enum_path, fields, etc);
 3001                      }
 3002                      _ => {
 3003                          let mut args: Vec<@Pat> = Vec::new();
 3004                          match self.token {
 3005                            token::LPAREN => {
 3006                              let is_star = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 3007                                  match *t {
 3008                                      token::BINOP(token::STAR) => true,
 3009                                      _ => false,
 3010                                  }
 3011                              });
 3012                              let is_dotdot = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 3013                                  match *t {
 3014                                      token::DOTDOT => true,
 3015                                      _ => false,
 3016                                  }
 3017                              });
 3018                              if is_star | is_dotdot {
 3019                                  // This is a "top constructor only" pat
 3020                                  self.bump();
 3021                                  if is_star {
 3022                                      self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteEnumWildcard);
 3023                                  }
 3024                                  self.bump();
 3025                                  self.expect(&token::RPAREN);
 3026                                  pat = PatEnum(enum_path, None);
 3027                              } else {
 3028                                  args = self.parse_enum_variant_seq(
 3029                                      &token::LPAREN,
 3030                                      &token::RPAREN,
 3031                                      seq_sep_trailing_disallowed(token::COMMA),
 3032                                      |p| p.parse_pat()
 3033                                  );
 3034                                  pat = PatEnum(enum_path, Some(args));
 3035                              }
 3036                            },
 3037                            _ => {
 3038                                if enum_path.segments.len() == 1 {
 3039                                    // it could still be either an enum
 3040                                    // or an identifier pattern, resolve
 3041                                    // will sort it out:
 3042                                    pat = PatIdent(BindByValue(MutImmutable),
 3043                                                    enum_path,

 3147      pub fn parse_stmt(&mut self, item_attrs: Vec<Attribute> ) -> @Stmt {

 3151              // If we have attributes then we should have an item
 3152              if found_attrs {
 3153                  p.span_err(p.last_span, "expected item after attributes");
 3154              }
 3155          }
 3156  
 3157          let lo = self.span.lo;
 3158          if self.is_keyword(keywords::Let) {
 3159              check_expected_item(self, !item_attrs.is_empty());

 3161              let decl = self.parse_let();

 3163          } else if is_ident(&self.token)
 3164              && !token::is_any_keyword(&self.token)

 3167              // overlap here; if this clause doesn't catch it (and it
 3168              // won't, for brace-delimited macros) it will fall through
 3169              // to the macro clause of parse_item_or_view_item. This

 3171

 3173              // rule here is deliberate, to allow macro users to use parens

 3177              // I could just be wrong.
 3178  
 3179              check_expected_item(self, !item_attrs.is_empty());

 3187                  token::special_idents::invalid // no special identifier
 3188              } else {

 3190              };
 3191  
 3192              // check that we're pointing at delimiters (need to check

 3194              // consuming more tokens).
 3195              let (bra, ket) = match self.token {
 3196                  token::LPAREN => (token::LPAREN, token::RPAREN),
 3197                  token::LBRACE => (token::LBRACE, token::RBRACE),

 3200                      // above.
 3201                      let ident_str = if id == token::special_idents::invalid {
 3202                          "identifier, "
 3203                      } else {
 3204                          ""
 3205                      };

 3210              };

 3213                  &bra,
 3214                  &ket,
 3215                  seq_sep_none(),
 3216                  |p| p.parse_token_tree()
 3217              );

 3219  
 3220              if id == token::special_idents::invalid {
 3221                  return @spanned(lo, hi, StmtMac(
 3222                      spanned(lo, hi, MacInvocTT(pth, tts, EMPTY_CTXT)), false));
 3223              } else {

 3225                  return @spanned(lo, hi, StmtDecl(
 3226                      @spanned(lo, hi, DeclItem(

 3228                              lo, hi, id /*id is good here*/,
 3229                              ItemMac(spanned(lo, hi, MacInvocTT(pth, tts, EMPTY_CTXT))),
 3230                              Inherited, Vec::new(/*no attrs*/)))),
 3231                      ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID));
 3232              }
 3233  
 3234          } else {
 3235              let found_attrs = !item_attrs.is_empty();
 3236              match self.parse_item_or_view_item(item_attrs, false) {
 3237                  IoviItem(i) => {
 3238                      let hi = i.span.hi;
 3239                      let decl = @spanned(lo, hi, DeclItem(i));
 3240                      return @spanned(lo, hi, StmtDecl(decl, ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID));

 3242                  IoviViewItem(vi) => {

 3244                                      "view items must be declared at the top of the block");
 3245                  }
 3246                  IoviForeignItem(_) => {
 3247                      self.fatal("foreign items are not allowed here");
 3248                  }
 3249                  IoviNone(_) => { /* fallthrough */ }

 3251  
 3252              check_expected_item(self, found_attrs);
 3253

 3255              let e = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_STMT_EXPR);

 3258      }

 3426      // matches optbounds = ( ( : ( boundseq )? )? )

 3433      fn parse_optional_ty_param_bounds(&mut self) -> Option<OwnedSlice<TyParamBound>> {
 3434          if !self.eat(&token::COLON) {
 3435              return None;
 3436          }

 3441                  token::LIFETIME(lifetime) => {

 3448                      }

 3451                  token::MOD_SEP | token::IDENT(..) => {
 3452                      let tref = self.parse_trait_ref();

 3456              }

 3466      // matches typaram = IDENT optbounds ( EQ ty )?

 4439                      |p| p.parse_ty(false)
 4440                  );

 4745      // this is the fall-through for parsing items.
 4746      fn parse_macro_use_or_failure(
 4747          &mut self,
 4748          attrs: Vec<Attribute> ,
 4749          macros_allowed: bool,
 4750          lo: BytePos,
 4751          visibility: Visibility
 4752      ) -> ItemOrViewItem {
 4753          if macros_allowed && !token::is_any_keyword(&self.token)
 4754                  && self.look_ahead(1, |t| *t == token::NOT)
 4755                  && (self.look_ahead(2, |t| is_plain_ident(t))
 4756                      || self.look_ahead(2, |t| *t == token::LPAREN)
 4757                      || self.look_ahead(2, |t| *t == token::LBRACE)) {
 4758              // MACRO INVOCATION ITEM
 4759  
 4760              // item macro.
 4761              let pth = self.parse_path(NoTypesAllowed).path;
 4762              self.expect(&token::NOT);

 4764              // a 'special' identifier (like what `macro_rules!` uses)
 4765              // is optional. We should eventually unify invoc syntax
 4766              // and remove this.
 4767              let id = if is_plain_ident(&self.token) {
 4768                  self.parse_ident()
 4769              } else {
 4770                  token::special_idents::invalid // no special identifier
 4771              };
 4772              // eat a matched-delimiter token tree:
 4773              let tts = match self.token {
 4774                  token::LPAREN | token::LBRACE => {
 4775                      let ket = token::flip_delimiter(&self.token);
 4776                      self.bump();
 4777                      self.parse_seq_to_end(&ket,
 4778                                            seq_sep_none(),
 4779                                            |p| p.parse_token_tree())
 4780                  }
 4781                  _ => self.fatal("expected open delimiter")
 4782              };
 4783              // single-variant-enum... :
 4784              let m = ast::MacInvocTT(pth, tts, EMPTY_CTXT);
 4785              let m: ast::Mac = codemap::Spanned { node: m,
 4786                                               span: mk_sp(self.span.lo,
 4787                                                           self.span.hi) };

 4789              let item = self.mk_item(lo,
 4790                                      self.last_span.hi,
 4791                                      id,
 4792                                      item_,
 4793                                      visibility,
 4794                                      attrs);

 4796          }

 4798          // FAILURE TO PARSE ITEM
 4799          if visibility != Inherited {
 4800              let mut s = ~"unmatched visibility `";
 4801              if visibility == Public {
 4802                  s.push_str("pub")
 4803              } else {
 4804                  s.push_str("priv")
 4805              }
 4806              s.push_char('`');
